commitResults.messageBody:
The original class name is a bit misleading, as it sounds like the class
is representing a single role instead of a collection of roles.

Therefore, it is renamed to ModuleRoleMap to indicate that it actually
represents the mapping between ModuleCode and RoleType, hence allows
better readability of the code

commitResults.messageBody:
Since now the find command demands at least one
name to be specified, arePrefixesPresent() will
be needed by both find and add. We need to avoid
code duplication and make sure it is only defined
once.

Let's move it to ParserUtil.java so that parsers for both add and find can access it.

Delete command only deletes one person as a time.

commitResults.messageTitle: Tweak output message and add more tests
commitResults.messageBody:
Output message for delete command is only for single element deletion.

Make output message fit mass deletion. Add test for parsing delete
command for mass deletion.

Duplicate handling only check name.

Change it to check email instead considering the possibility of people
with exact same name. Email is unique and compulsory in the context of
the app.

commitResults.messageBody: Create a class representing a map from ModuleCode to RoleType

Find command now support finding contacts based on module-role with
prefix r/, e.g. find r/cs1101s-ta.
If role is not specified, student is assumed.
When multiple inputs are given, e.g. find r/cs1101s-ta r/cs1231s n/Ben,
contacts matching any of the keywords given will be shown.

find n/name r/module-role only finds matching module-role.

Refine the logic such that find n/name r/module-role finds contacts with
matching name AND module-role.
